{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CdH7AxLUmudHbU9be6k9y","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fixed. Both tests pass.\n\n## The bug\n\n`src/money.js` applied the discount and rounded to the nearest cent **per line**, then summed:\n\n```js\ntotal += Math.round(line.unitCents * line.qty * (1 - discountPct / 100));\n```\n\nBut the spec (and billing's expectation) is that the discount applies to the **order subtotal**, rounded **once**. Per-line rounding lets each line's fractional cent round up independently, and those roundings accumulate into a whole-cent overcharge.\n\nFor the reported case — two $5.00 lines at 10.1% off — each line computes `449.5`, which `Math.round` bumps up to `450`, summing to **900 (`$9.00`)**. Correctly discounting the `1000c` subtotal once gives `1000 × 0.899 = 899` → **`$8.99`**.\n\n## The fix\n\nSum the exact integer subtotal first, then apply the discount and round a single time:\n\n```js\nlet subtotal = 0;\nfor (const line of lines) {\n  subtotal += line.unitCents * line.qty;\n}\nreturn Math.round(subtotal * (1 - discountPct / 100));\n```\n\nI also added a regression test capturing the exact `$9.00`-vs-`$8.99` scenario."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":309,"cache_read_input_tokens":24677,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":309},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f58ed6f5-fc23-4dbb-88a1-b5945d3588af","uuid":"37b992fa-96c9-4f79-9bc1-796bf0f7a04b","timestamp":"2026-07-22T12:37:02.159Z","request_id":"req_011CdH7AwE1AqFkHeQGuSbrU"}
